add this static method to code whether internet is available or not 

    public static boolean isNetworkAvailable(Context context) {
        ConnectivityManager connectivityManager = (ConnectivityManager) context.getApplicationContext().getSystemService(Context.CONNECTIVITY_SERVICE);
        NetworkInfo activeNetworkInfo = connectivityManager.getActiveNetworkInfo();
        return activeNetworkInfo != null &amp;&amp; activeNetworkInfo.isConnected();
    }

**Suggestion :** check through **isNetworkAvailable()** wherever you required to check network if it return true then do further task else you can show alertdialog regarding checking connection again

Using ```ConnectivityManager``` you can check for connection type and state and return it via a method call. This can be used when logging in for example:

    public static int getConnectivityState(Context context) {
            final ConnectivityManager connectivityManager = (ConnectivityManager) context.getSystemService(Context.CONNECTIVITY_SERVICE);
            final NetworkInfo networkInfo = connectivityManager .getActiveNetworkInfo();

            if (networkInfo != null) {
                if(networkInfo.getType().equals(ConnectivityManager.TYPE_WIFI))
                    return TYPE_WIFI;
    
                if(networkInfo getType().equals(ConnectivityManager.TYPE_MOBILE))
                    return TYPE_MOBILE;
            } 
            return TYPE_NOT_CONNECTED;
        }

To listen to network changes throughout your application, you need a broadcast receiver that has an intent filter on the action ```CONNECTIVITY_CHANGE```:

    IntentFilter intentFilter = new IntentFilter(&quot;android.net.conn.CONNECTIVITY_CHANGE&quot;);
    context.registerReceiver(new NetworkBroadcastReceiver(), intentFilter);

on API level 24 or higher you must register this receiver with ```context.registerReceiver``` instead of declaring it in the manifest.

[Futher reading](https://developer.android.com/reference/android/net/ConnectivityManager)

